      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 51: When push notifications are disabled while the app is backgrounded, this queues restoreProxyAccountsAfterBackground() before setPushNotificationConfig()/setProxyEnabled(false), but JamiApplicationFirebase.pushToken is also likely set/cleared through mDeviceService and its setter immediately calls restoreProxyAccountsAfterBackground() again without the same FIFO guarantee relative to setProxyEnabled(false). If that restore runs after proxy has been disabled, AccountService.restoreProxyAccountsAfterBackground() treats the ids as terminal and drops them while still inactive, leaving accounts unreachable. Make push-disable restoration a single ordered operation on AccountService\u0027s executor, or expose an AccountService method that restores then disables proxy in one executor task.\n```suggestion\nmAccountService.disablePushAndRestoreBackgroundAccounts(\n    token?.first ?: \"\",\n    token?.second ?: \"\",\n    mDeviceService.pushPlatform\n)\n```",
